.SH "NAME"
mysql_waitpid \- bust a cap up in process n' wait fo' its termination
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'\fBmysql_waitpid\ [\fR\fB\fIoptions\fR\fR\fB]\ \fR\fB\fIpid\fR\fR\fB\ \fR\fB\fIwait_time\fR\fR\ 'u
\fBmysql_waitpid [\fR\fB\fIoptions\fR\fR\fB] \fR\fB\fIpid\fR\fR\fB \fR\fB\fIwait_time\fR\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
\fBmysql_waitpid\fR
signals a process ta terminizzle n' waits fo' tha process ta exit\&. Well shiiiit, it uses the
kill()
system call n' Unix signals, so it runs on Unix n' Unix\-like systems\&.
.PP
Invoke
\fBmysql_waitpid\fR
like this:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
shell> \fBmysql_waitpid [\fR\fB\fIoptions\fR\fR\fB] \fR\fB\fIpid\fR\fR\fB \fR\fB\fIwait_time\fR\fR
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.PP
\fBmysql_waitpid\fR
sendz signal 0 ta tha process identified by
\fIpid\fR
and waits up to
\fIwait_time\fR
secondz fo' tha process ta terminate\&.
\fIpid\fR
and
\fIwait_time\fR
must be positizzle integers\&.
.PP
If process termination occurs within tha wait time or tha process do not exist,
\fBmysql_waitpid\fR
returns 0\&. Otherwise, it returns 1\&.
.PP
If the
kill()
system call cannot handle signal 0,
\fBmysql_waitpid()\fR
uses signal 1 instead\&.
.PP
